Boudou Says Argentina Still Talking With Paris Club on Debt

-- B y   S i l v i a   M a r t i n e z
-- 
2011-05-19T23:04:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/boudou-says-argentina-still-talking-with-paris-club-on-debt-1-.html
Argentina ’s Economy Minister  Amado Boudou  said that the government remains in negotiations with the
 Paris Club  group of creditor nations.  “The talks are challenging and have many aspects,” Boudou
told reporters in  Buenos Aires  today.  La Nacion newspaper yesterday reported that Argentina is
seeking to pay off about $8.4 billion in defaulted debt to the
Paris Club over a period of up to six years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Silvia Martinez in Buenos Aires at 
 smartinez19@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Robert Jameson at 
 rjameson@bloomberg.net  